// @emit-error ref-list field element type is not interned
// Floor (compiler-crash guard): the deep variant-box arm from fuzz sweep zq0NPY multiobs,
// seed 24438928 — a union whose struct arm nests a struct-element ARRAY whose element struct
// carries a nullable-STRUCT field, a map-of-map field, AND a nullable-f64-LIST field, beside
// `{f}`-fieldset twins. The nullable-list element struct is an unsupported array element (the
// whole family loud-rejects everywhere), but this SPELLING crashed the compiler: interning the
// inline union-arm shape (`internInlineShape`) pushes the struct header, then computes a code-5
// ref-list field's element name (`refArrElemName`), which RE-ENTERS `structIndexOfTypeName` —
// whose scan read the half-registered shape's not-yet-appended `sFieldElemName` rows OUT OF
// BOUNDS (an `out of bounds array access` compiler TRAP). Now the scanner skips structs whose
// field rows are incomplete, so the family fails LOUDLY (the type section's un-interned
// ref-list element reject) rather than trapping the compiler. Distinct from the minimal
// `emitObj` guard (error-nullable-list-field-struct-array-element.vl): with only that guard
// this deep spelling still crashed in the shape-collection pass.
function useIt(
  p: {a: {a: {f: boolean} | null, f: {[string]: {[string]: i64}}, z: f64[] | null}[], f: {f: i64}, z: {f: boolean}} | string | {q: i64},
) {
  print(0)
}
function go() { useIt("other") }
go()
